J1.2.DialogLine: Aliya! I need you to come knead this dough so I can give it time to rise.

J1.4.DialogLine: I’ll be right there, Mom.  Give me a minute.

J1.1.1.DialogLine: Where do you think you’re going young lady?

J1.1.3.DialogLine: Get over here and get this dough rolled out.

J2.3.DialogLine: What happened last night?  I remember Yvonna bringing me over to the party you guys threw me last night with all of my friends.

J2.4.DialogLine: … I remember waiting for something to happen, for my ability to come through.

J2.6.DialogLine: *Looks over at Kahrin with a concerned look*

J2.7.DialogLine: Honey, we think your ability came in full force during the party.

J2.8.DialogLine: You kept saying something about seeing colors and lines…

J2.9.DialogLine: You passed out after that.  Kahrin and Yvonna got you to bed and Yvonna made us promise her that we would let her know if anything more happened to you.

J2.11.DialogLine: Yep, and you’re lucky you didn’t whack your head on anything on your way to the ground.

J2.14.DialogLine: Anyway, Yvonna is really worried about you and kept coming over every few minutes this morning to see if you were up.

J2.15.DialogLine: Why don’t you head over if you’re feeling up to it?

J2.17.DialogLine: Yeah, I think I’ll go find her.  Did she say where she was going last time she was over?

J2.18.DialogLine: She was headed towards the metalshop, but that was an hour ago, so she might not be there anymore.

J2.20.DialogLine: Love you two, see you later.

J2.22.DialogLine: Love you, dork.  Go have fun.

J3.1a.DialogLine: Go have fun, Aliya.  Kahrin and I need to work.

J3.1c.DialogLine: What are you still doing here?

K1.2.DialogLine: Yeah but my head still hurts a bit.  What’s with all the baking?

K1.3.DialogLine: We need to restock the bakery after the party last night.

K1.4.DialogLine: I don’t have time to talk right now, dear.  I need to get these scones put together before the butter melts.

K3.1b.DialogLine: If you stay any longer, I’m going to put you to work.

Y1.1.DialogLine: Yvonna!  Shouldn’t you be at the shop?

Y1.4.DialogLine: I’ve been by your house, I don’t know how many times!

Y1.5.DialogLine: Your moms kept saying to come back later.

Y1.7.DialogLine: And when I go back to check on you, you’re not even there!

Y1.8.DialogLine: Why didn’t you come find me!

Y1.10.DialogLine: I just woke up like twenty minutes ago and my moms told me you had been by.

Y1.11.DialogLine: Oh…  Sorry, but I was worried about you…

Y1.12.DialogLine: What the hell happened last night?

Y1.13.DialogLine: One second you were telling me you felt weird…

Y1.14.DialogLine: Then the next you were passed out on the ground.

Y1.15.DialogLine: I had to carry you up to your bed, and you’re heavy!

Y1.20.DialogLine: I remember the party last night and this heat that started coursing through me.

Y1.21.DialogLine: My vision started flashing in and out before everything went black.

Y1.23.DialogLine: Do you think it was your power coming through?

Y1.26.DialogLine: When I woke up to help my moms… I noticed that there was this red…

Y1.28.DialogLine: Hmm… It looked a lot like a thread and it connected them together.

Y1.30.DialogLine: You sure you didn’t hit your head when you passed out?

Y1.31.DialogLine: … Even if I did, that wouldn’t change what I saw.

Y1.32.DialogLine: So a red thread that connected them…

Y1.33.DialogLine: Do you think it means something?

Y1.34.DialogLine: Maybe… something that ties them together…

Y1.37.DialogLine: It’s their love!  Their love for each other!

Y1.38.DialogLine: I think I saw their love.

Y1.39.DialogLine: Huh, interesting power.  I wonder if you can see other types of threads.

Y1.41.DialogLine: Like… crushes!  You know how Sonke has been mooning over Ori since forever?

Y1.43.DialogLine: I wonder if you could see a thread that connects Sonke to Ori.

Y1.44.DialogLine: Ooooo that reminds me!  I think Ori likes Sonke back!

Y1.45.DialogLine: Wait really?  Did he tell you?

Y1.48.DialogLine: It kinda slipped out of him at breakfast.

Y1.49.DialogLine: You sure it just slipped out?

Y1.50.DialogLine: Anyway… maybe you should go see if we were right about your power.

Y1.51.DialogLine: I guess… you stay here though.  I don’t wanna have to spend the rest of the day trying to find you again.

Y2.1.DialogLine: I said I wasn’t going to go anywhere!  Stop checking up on me.

Y3.1.DialogLine: So what happened?  Did my brother confess?

Y3.3.DialogLine: Why don’t you go find out yourself?

Y3.4.DialogLine: Really, Aliya?  Did you even find anything out?

Y3.5.DialogLine: I did a lot more than that...

L0.1.DialogLine: Why isn’t this damn store open!

L1.1.DialogLine: Why isn’t this damn store open!

L1.2.DialogLine: Sylvie promised me she would get me that new ointment she concocted!

L1.4.DialogLine: No! It rained the other day and I didn’t cover my leg well enough, so the damn joints are all rusted up.

L1.4.1.DialogLine: Managed to get some sores too which is why I need the ointment.

L1.5.DialogLine: I don’t have the time to make new joints because of that caravan that is coming in a few days.

L1.6.DialogLine: Ori’s already working overtime and I promised Yvonna the day off.

L1.7.DialogLine: Not to be rude, but did you need something?

L1.8a1.DialogLine: Have you seen Sonke around the shop lately?

choices.playerChoiceLine: I heard a rumor that Ori has a crush on Sonke.
I heard Sonke was recently spending more time around your shop, do you know why?

L1.8aa3.DialogLine: You know I kinda had a feeling that he felt that way.

L1.8aa4.DialogLine: How do you know that?  Did he say something?

L1.8aa5.DialogLine: Well… Sonke was by the other day and he didn’t speak to me, just went straight to Ori’s station to watch him work.

L1.8aa6.DialogLine: Ori usually brushes him off, but he didn’t this time.

L1.8aa8.DialogLine: Ori’s in the shop right now, why don’t you ask him about this?

L1.8aa9.DialogLine: I’m giving Sylvie a few more minutes before I dismantle the doorknob.

L1.8ab1.DialogLine: Well… Sonke was by the other day and he didn’t speak to me, just went straight to Ori’s station to watch him work.

L1.8ab2.DialogLine: Ori usually brushes him off, but he didn’t this time.

L1.8ab4.DialogLine: Ori’s in the shop right now, why don’t you ask him about this?

L1.8ab5.DialogLine: I’m giving Sylvie a few more minutes before I dismantle the doorknob.

L1.8b1.DialogLine: How has Ori’s work been going?

L1.8b2.DialogLine: He’s been awesome!  I’m surprised at how well he’s handling all the extra work I’ve been giving him.

L1.8b3.DialogLine: He practically lives in the shop since we got that big order, but I’ve heard no complaints.

L1.8b4.DialogLine: Wow, I guess he never gets distracted then.

L1.8b5.DialogLine: Well, Sonke’s been coming by more than usual.

L1.8b6.DialogLine: I try to get him to leave because I can’t afford for us to fall behind on these projects.

L1.8b7.DialogLine: But, he usually sticks around for a bit to watch Ori work.

L1.8b8.DialogLine: Actually, come to think of it, Ori let Sonke stay for awhile last time.

L1.8b10.DialogLine: Ori’s in the shop right now, why don’t you ask him about this?  Just don’t distract him too much.

L1.8b11.DialogLine: I’m giving Sylvie a few more minutes before I dismantle the doorknob.

L2.1a.DialogLine: Sylvie!  Get out here and open this door!

L2.1b.DialogLine: Damn screw won't come out of the doorknob...

L2.1c.DialogLine: Crap!  Can't move my damn knee now...

Lo0.1.DialogLine: Wonder when Sylvie’s gonna open up the shop for the day.

Lo1.1.DialogLine: That damnable girl has gone and done it again!

Lo1.2.DialogLine: Why can’t she take better care of herself…

Lo1.4.DialogLine: What? Aliya? What are you doing here? Shouldn’t you be helping your parents in the bakery?

Lo1.5.DialogLine: They gave me the day off today.

Lo1.6.DialogLine: Ah, then what are you doing wasting it talking to me?

Lo1.7.DialogLine: Shouldn’t you be off having fun with Yvonna?  You two are as thick as thieves.

Lo1.8.DialogLine: Yeah…  Were you talking about Leena just now?

Lo1.9.DialogLine: Can’t slip anything by you, can I?

Lo1.10.DialogLine: When Leena gets into her work, she tends to forget about everything else… including herself.

Lo1.11.DialogLine: Her damn prosthetic is basically useless now since all the joints are rusted over and she managed to overwork herself so she has sores there too.

Lo1.12.DialogLine: That and her mooning over that kid that has eyes on someone else.  Silly girl is just a pile of troubles, but I love her anyway.

Lo1.14.DialogLine: Huh? Oh, you’re still here.  Don’t mention that to anyone please?

Lo1.15.DialogLine: Leena will have my head if she finds out I told someone.

choices.playerChoiceLine: Uh… sure.  My lips are sealed.
Leena has a crush on someone?

Lo1.17a1.DialogLine: Thanks, now get going.  You don’t want to hang around by me all day.

Lo1.17b2.DialogLine: I mean, they’re good friends right?  They’ve been friends forever and…

Lo1.17b4.DialogLine: I’m not going to discuss it.  Run along now, or I’ll be having a talk with Jocelyn and Kahrin about you and your damn curiosity.

Lo1.17c1.DialogLine: Drop it, Aliya.  If Leena wanted you to know, she would have told you.

Lo1.17c2.DialogLine: Alright, alright.  See ya later, Lozu.

Lo2.1.DialogLine: Wonder when Sylvie’s gonna open up the shop for the day.

S0.1.DialogLine: Mara! We’re gonna need some more lemons out at the bar.

S1.2.DialogLine: Aliya!  Give me a sec, gotta finish cleanin first.

S1.4.DialogLine: Alrighty, all clean!  Now wha didja wanna talk abou’.

S1.5.DialogLine: Yvonna told me something this morning…

S1.8.DialogLine: Spit it out, Aliya. I don have all day, ya know.  Got places to be later.

choices.playerChoiceLine: Yvonna told me that she heard Ori say that he likes you!
Wait.. where are you going later?

S1.10a4.DialogLine: Apparently he let it slip over breakfast.

S1.10a5.DialogLine: I wonder why he never said anything before?

S1.10a6.DialogLine: I’m ova at the metal shop at least once a week, gettin new rings fashioned for my power.

S1.10a7.DialogLine: Meybe he’s shy.  I know he’s been busy lately, what with all those things to make for the caravan comin in soon.

S1.10a8.DialogLine: Maybe he’s been waiting for you to say something.

S1.10a9.DialogLine: You aren’t the most forward person.  All you talk about is your electricity.

S1.10a10.DialogLine: Yeah… Did I tell you that Leena got some new metal that conducts the lightning better?

S1.10a11.DialogLine: Much easier to control the sparks now.

S1.10a12.DialogLine: Sonke.. we were talking about Ori.

S1.10a14.DialogLine: What do you think I should do?  Should I talk to him?

choices.playerChoiceLine: Wait.. where are you going later?

S1.10a15a1.DialogLine: I had a meetin with him anyway today.

S1.10a15a2.DialogLine: Leena put him on the job of makin those new rings for me an I wanna help design ‘em.

S1.10a15a3.DialogLine: I betta finish up here first though.  Gotta get the work done.

S1.10a15a4.DialogLine: Ok, Sonke.  I’ll let you get back to work.  See you later.

S1.10a15a5.DialogLine: See ya later, Aliya!  Thanks for the news.

S1.10a15b1.DialogLine: You think so?  I don wanna scare him off…

S1.10a15b2.DialogLine: I know he loves his work and can get caught up in it.

S1.10a15b3.DialogLine: I don’ want him to feel that I’m takin him away from that.

S1.10a15b4.DialogLine: It might be best for now.  Especially since he’s so busy with that caravan coming in soon.

S1.10a15b5.DialogLine: Yeah… I’ll make sure to let him alone while he’s workin when I’m over there later.

S1.10a15b6.DialogLine: Gotta finish cleanin here though ‘fore I can go ova.

S1.10a15b7.DialogLine: I’m going to head out Sonke.  I’ll talk to you later.

S1.10b1.DialogLine: Gotta swing by the metal shop.

S1.10b2.DialogLine: Leena got some new metal in that’ll make it easier ta control my power.

S1.10b3.DialogLine: Keeps the lightnin sparks to a minimum.

S1.10b4.DialogLine: Cause I’ve been havin trouble controllin the more delicate stuff, if you know what I mean.

S1.10b6.DialogLine: Well its real simple ta get a big lightning strike goin, but makin something small…

S1.10b7.DialogLine: That takes a lot of control an the rings I have now don’ help much.

S1.10b8.DialogLine: I’ve been wantin to try an make little bits of lightnin’, where they don have as much power as the big ones.

S1.10b9.DialogLine: But, yeah, I wanna help design the new rings.

S1.10b10.DialogLine: Meybe, I’ll stay an watch them work for a bit.

S1.10b11.DialogLine: I betta finish up here first though.  Gotta get the work done.

S1.10b12.DialogLine: Ok, Sonke.  I’ll let you get back to work.  See you later.

S2.1a.DialogLine: Why won’t this stain come out?

S2.1b.DialogLine: Mara! We’re gonna need some more lemons out at the bar.

S2.1c.DialogLine: Can’t wait to get over to the metal shop.

M0.1.DialogLine: The bar’s closed, Aliya.  Come back once we’re all cleaned up.

M1.1.DialogLine: Sonke, you better get this bar ship shape within the hour!

M1.3.DialogLine: The bar’s closed, Aliya.  Come back once we’re all cleaned up.

M2.2.DialogLine: The bar’s still closed, Aliya.  Unless you want to be put to work getting ready for the dinner rush?

M2.3.DialogLine: In which case, I'll be happy to have the help.

M2.4.DialogLine: No, I’m good.  I’ll stay out of your way.

O0.1.DialogLine: Why won't this damn clock work?

O1.2.DialogLine: Can’t talk right now.  Need to get this order finished before Leena gets back.

O1.3.DialogLine: Uh… ok.  I’ll come back later.

O2.1.DialogLine: Hey Ori.  Manage to get that order finished?

O2.2.DialogLine: Oh hey Aliya.  Just finished it actually.

O2.3.DialogLine: Was there something you wanted to talk about?

choices.playerChoiceLine: I heard from Yvonna that you have feelings for Sonke.
I hear that Sonke’s coming over later.
I heard from Leena that Sonke’s been over a lot.

O2.5a2.DialogLine: I let one thing slip and next thing the whole town knows.

O2.5a3.DialogLine: What else did my sister share with you?

O2.5a4.DialogLine: Uh…  That was mainly it.  She was ecstatic.

O2.5a5.DialogLine: Has she done anythin with her news, besides tellin you?

O2.5a6.DialogLine: No… But, I was just over at the bar, talking with Sonke.

choices.playerChoiceLine: I kinda told him and he was so happy to hear that you felt the same way as he did.
I told him, but I think he’s going to wait for you to make the first move.
Nothing really.  Though he told me he’s coming over later.

O2.5a9a3.DialogLine: Yeah he does.  You didn’t know?

O2.5a9a4.DialogLine: No.  I’ve been so wrapped up in my work tha I didna even notice.

O2.5a9a5.DialogLine: He’s coming over later to help design his new lightning rings.

O2.5a9a7.DialogLine: Yeah…  Maybe some good has finally come from Yvonna’s meddling!

O2.5a9a8.DialogLine: I’ll leave you to it then.

O2.5a9b2.DialogLine: So, that must mean he feels the same way?

O2.5a9b3.DialogLine: That’s what I got from talking to him.

O2.5a9b4.DialogLine: Well then, I guess I’ll need to bring it up, next time I see him.

O2.5a9b6.DialogLine: I think you should do it sooner rather than later.

O2.5a9b7.DialogLine: You both have obvious feelings for each other.

O2.5a9b8.DialogLine: Yeah…  Maybe some good has finally come from Yvonna’s meddling!

O2.5a9b9.DialogLine: I’ll leave you to it then.

O2.5a9c1.DialogLine: He couldn’t stop talking about the new rings that he’s getting made.

O2.5a9c3.DialogLine: No, I figured that that was your business.

O2.5a9c5.DialogLine: Best ta leave it as it is.  I don’t have time for anythin right now besides work.

O2.5a9c6.DialogLine: Leena is finally givin me more responsibility and I don’ wanna let her down.

O2.5a9c7.DialogLine: You aren’t going to tell him either?

O2.5a9c8.DialogLine: No… I don’ wanna mess with what we have already.

O2.5a9c9.DialogLine: What if he doesn’t feel the same way?

O2.5a9c12.DialogLine: Oh man!  Look at the time.

O2.5a9c13.DialogLine: Leena’s gonna be back anytime now.

O2.5a9c15.DialogLine: I’ll talk to ya later Aliya.

O2.5b1.DialogLine: Yeah, Leena got in a new metal that should help his electric power.

O2.5b2.DialogLine: He was really excited when I told him.

O2.5b3.DialogLine: Kept tryin to show me this new trick he learned.  It was pretty cool when he finally got it to work.

O2.5b5.DialogLine: I can’t wait until he gets here.  I need ta tell him somethin.

O2.5b6.DialogLine: Yvonna overheard me trying to figure out what I was gonna say to him.

O2.5b7.DialogLine: I know.  Yvonna told me a little while ago.

O2.5b8.DialogLine: Why does Yvonna need ta share every little thing I do?

O2.5b10.DialogLine: The whole town already knows that Sonke has feelings for you.

O2.5b11.DialogLine: It’s been kinda amusing that you haven’t noticed this whole time.

O2.5b14.DialogLine: Cause I wasn’t sure.  I wanted time ta figure out what I felt for him, ya know.

O2.5b15.DialogLine: Not just rush into it blind.

O2.5b16.DialogLine: So what are you going to do now?

O2.5b17.DialogLine: I don’t know.  Figured I’d let him make the first move.

O2.5b19.DialogLine: Don’t worry about it, Aliya.  I’ll find some way ta push him in the right direction.

O2.5b20.DialogLine: Now get going back to my gossiping sister.  I’ve no doubt she’s gonna want to hear a full report.

O2.5b21.DialogLine: Who says I’m going to give it to her.

O2.5c2.DialogLine: Been so busy lately what with all the orders that we need ta finish for the caravan.

O2.5c3.DialogLine: She told me that he was over the other day and came over to watch you work.

O2.5c4.DialogLine: I remember him bein here, but the clock that I was workin on took all my focus.

O2.5c5.DialogLine: That reminds me…  Leena wanted me to get that new metal heated up ‘fore she got back.

O2.5c6.DialogLine: Sorry, Aliya.  But I need to get back to work.

O2.5c7.DialogLine: No big deal, Ori.  Yvonna and I have plans for today anyway.

O3.1.DialogLine: Yvonna told me earlier that she was gonna meet you in the town center.

O3.2.DialogLine: Don't wanna keep her waiting too long, Aliya.

O3.3.DialogLine: Yeah, I know.  She gets grumpy when I don't go find her right away.

Su1.1.DialogLine: Yeah, I know.  She gets grumpy when I don't go find her right away.

J1.1.DialogLine: Hey Aliya.  You ok after last night?

J1.3.DialogLine: Well that’s good.  Did you need something in here?

J1.4.DialogLine: No, thanks though.  My moms are restocking the bakery after the party they threw for me last night…

J1.5.DialogLine: Hey, would you happen to know where Yvonna is?

J1.6.DialogLine: My moms told me she had been by this morning several times.

J1.7.DialogLine: I haven’t seen her today.  I’ve been busy here taking inventory for Roth since he left on a business trip.

J1.8.DialogLine: Ok.  I need to talk to her about last night so I’ll get going.  Good luck with inventory.

J2.1.DialogLine: Where did Roth leave those bags of vegetables we just got in from Surrel?
